title.narrative: By 2021, improved MOH capacity for EPI

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the country's immunization services through outreach services. Support was also provided to MoH in strengthening the immunization supply chain system at the lowest delivery service point, especially in high risk and low performing areas, through establishment of permanent immunization service delivery points, thus reducing dependency on costly outreach services. A CCEOP rehabilitation plan has reinforced the immunization programme across the whole country. A total of USD 2.25 mio. has been leveraged as a co-investment between MoH and GAVI to strengthen the cold chain system nationally, especially in 70 hard to reach districts of 15 provinces. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
